name: Canggu Wooden Green Paradise
address: Br. Pempatan, Jl. Sahadewa, Munggu, Kec. Mengwi, Kabupaten Badung, Bali 80351, Indonesia
review 1: LOVE my experience to stay in this place. The only thing I wish it was better, I stayed when they were upgrading to have more rooms. So there's that. But the rest, It was amazing!! The Staff was amazing and friendly. The room is clean. I booked the one with the private pool and I could bring my dog. And of course, I recommend this place for my friend from USA and she loves it as well
review 2: My recent stay at Canggu Green Gate Paradise was far from enjoyable. The hotel was more of a nightmare than a paradise, with constant construction noise starting as early as 7 am each day. The photos online painted a much more appealing picture than the reality I experienced. The cleanliness and upkeep of the facilities left much to be desired, and the dated amenities made for an uncomfortable stay. The inconsistent water pressure and temperature only added to the discomfort. Given the price paid, the value for money was severely lacking. The breakfast was also a letdown. The beds were incredibly uncomfortable, the hair dryer lacked power, and the room lacked basic amenities. To make matters worse, the toilet flooded whenever it rained, and the mosquito nets and soft furnishings were visibly dated and unclean. Overall, I would strongly advise against staying at this hotel.
review 3:
Lovely place to stay. Very courteous, professional staff. Rooms were clean and well looked after. Pool was clean and pleasant. Right next to a rice field, so sunset is beautiful. Around a 15-20 minute bike to Canggu beach.

The only thing I would say is currently noisy, due to construction next door, but won‚Äôt effect my review
review 4: Great place. Value for money! Huge open garden space. Nice dimensions swimming pool. Super clean, very friendly people and quiet. Will definitely come back!
review 5: Delighted with that villa, the room was beautiful, clean and very cozy, the people were very kind and friendly. I will return without a doubt. A special thanks to the manager who let us to left our luggage there for some days üòç

review 1:
This is amazing!
Food was so delicious ü§§& affordable ! Spacious place beautiful design, they have table tennis üèì & pool table.
Customer Service top üëçüèΩ the music üéµ.. really nice playlist.
Definitely a must when in the area
review 2: The place and the food are good but the thing is the staff there are maybe not enough or what I don‚Äôt know. have to wait for 30 minutes for my food. But i love it
review 3: Food here is so so good, very authentic and full of flavour! The suya is delicious, the Jollof rice and friend chicken is 10/10. The staff here are also very friendly and bring a good energy to your dining experience
review 4:
I'll update my review. I don‚Äôt know what exactly affected it, but the music really became quieter and so far it hasn‚Äôt bothered me anymore. I want to express my gratitude for this. I hope it will be so. I wish you success.

I appeal to the owners of this establishment. You have absolutely no respect for the place you are in. This place has an incredible atmosphere of silence,  comfort. I don't mind parties as long as they last until 12 midnight. But yours music is loud until 2-3 am. In response to our request to make it at least a little quieter, we received a strict refusal and referred to police permission. But let's use common sense. Your music is not just loud, it's deafening. You're preventing construction workers from resting after a hard day's work, scaring animals, and preventing everyone in the area from sleeping. If you have even a little self-respect, you can find an opportunity to turn down the volume a little. I ask for little, just to make it quieter. Your guests will also be grateful, since this level of noise makes it difficult to communicate and damages the eardrums. I hope for your prudence and understanding üôèüèº
review 5: The service was super super nice, the server were all friendly, the waiting time was long because it was freshly made, and you can adjust your spicy level too. I was having fufu (cassava) with egusi (beef) next time I‚Äôd try it with fish. At first the egusi tasted unusual because it was my first time tasting it, took me time to like it, but now I love itüíó cant wait to come back. The price was totally worth it!

name: Victory Munggu
address: 949C+MVJ, Munggu, Mengwi, Badung Regency, Bali 80351, Indonesia
review 1:
Really nice place in Munggu.
15 minutes by motorbike from Canggu and 7 minutes by motorbike from a really nice beach.
A lot of warungs, restaurants and mini marts nearby.
Staff very kind and clean rooms. They offer to clean the room every day.
Fantastic view on the rice fields
Recommended
review 2:
incredibly nice staff and extremely clean
Cosy wooden bungalows in the middle of rice fields. Small pool to cool off, very nicely planted between the bungalows. super comfortable mattress and a fantastic soundscape at night from the rice fields.
but what makes this place are the people who work here, i always love coming back and it feels like home!

sampai jumpa lagi
Made Agung Andi:)
review 3:
Such a great place to stay!
Staff very friendly,
Confortable room and good mattress and beautiful pool!
Quiet area just near by the center.
Hardly recommend !
review 4: We stayed here a couple of nights and really enjoyed it! Very clean, great AC and comfy bed! Staff was very kind!
review 5: We had a lovely stay in Victory Munggu where the staff is very friendly and attentive to every need, the whole premise is very clean and quiet. If we come to Bali next time, we will come back for sure!

name: Jay India Bali
address: Jl. Sahadewa I, Munggu, Kec. Mengwi, Kabupaten Badung, Bali 80351, Indonesia
review 1: We were searching for an Indian restaurant and found this hidden gem near to Tanah lot temple around 7 km. The taste and quantity was good with reasonable price. The place is bit small but that should not stop you from visiting this .
review 2: Really good option to stop and eat. The food and atmosfera is so healing. The owner has an incredible soul! I recommend it 100%. Thanks madeüôè‚ú®
review 3:
Great Indian food served at a venue in Munggu, just west of Canggu on the way to Tanah Lot, overlooking a beautiful view of paddy fields.

Came here for dinner to taste their Thali sets, along with a side of Butter Chicken (and a cheeky Singaraja). Was not disappointed at all, and ended up being a most filling and delicious meal to close the evening.

Pak Made who served me was so kind and attentive, and their pet dogs there were lovely to have for company.

Reasonably priced, plenty of parking for both cars and motorcycles, awesome service, great vibes.
review 4: Wow what a feed..... The value for money here is off the chain. And also a nice view to boot. There was no one here when we got here just to arrive at a steep staircase to go upstairs, was greeted by beautiful views of the rice fields. Ordered up, food was quick and wow, butter chicken, saffron rice and naan bread always my favourite combo and a serving of the chicken taquitos. Was delicious!! Just wanted to eat more. Girlfriend wasn't too hungry so just got the juicy chicken tacos and I tried and were delightful. And the best thing about this I the price big portions you will not walk out hungry. Please go enjoy this place you will not regret it.
review 5: Its very nice having an Indian food nearby that taste nice and cheap. Satisfied with the portion tooüëç

name: Kayu Bali
address: cemagi, Jalan raya, Cemagi, Kec. Mengwi, Kabupaten Badung, Bali 80351, Indonesia
review 1: Beautifully kept oasis away from the hustle & bustle yet close enough to the beaches and great cafes.  From the moment we enquired, we felt welcomed. The hosts are incredibly helpful and nothing is too much. I was travelling with my daughter so we wanted a place that was safe & secure.  We always felt safe and like we were coming home. The rooms are spotless and the pool area is the perfect place to unwind.  We had such a great time and would definetly return. Thank you Katja & Ivan for making our Bali stay so special. You guys are great and have created a wonderful place to stay in Bali.
review 2:
This is the most amazing, quiet, accommodating and heartwarming place i have stayed at in Bali.
Hosts, Ivan and Katja, are caring, sweet and helpful.
Rooms and pool are clean and guesthouses are true to the balinese style. Coming from the streets noice to this oasis, is like heaven.
You will need some transportation to get around, but even that, Katja og Ivan are helpful with. The place have scooters to rent.
The area has a lot of eating options, rice fields and 10 min to the beach.
Tanah Lot 15 min. Canggu 20 min.
I can highly recommend this beautiful place.
You will feel at home - i did.
review 3: Our stay at Kayu Bali was the highlight of our 3 week tour through Bali! Romantic, authentic decor with all modern luxury. Wonderful beds and a nice refreshing swimming pool in a beautiful garden. Host Ivan took us twice to take surfing lessons which was really awesome! we have rented motorbikes through them and have been able to explore the beautiful island. We really had a blast, partly due to the good care of the host and hostess. We received many tips and were looked after as if we were friends. We're definitely  coming back to this place when we  visit Bali again!
review 4: Really lovely accommodation! The host is very friendly and helpful! The cottages are super cute and very clean. I love the location, 20min walk to the beach or 10min drive to Canggu trough rice fields and bac alleys. I would recommend anyone to stay here :)
review 5: Amazing place, authentic indonesian wooden houses are so comfortable, love it. Beautiful garden with swimming pool. Quite area, but not far from main canggu show, was just right for romantic getaway.

review 2: Their pizzas are incredible! They beat some of the bigger more well known pizza joints by far!! The buratta pizza is my delicious and such value for money. Do yourself a favor and give it a try üëèüèª

review 4: Hi to all customers of vignando an future clients  of this new place.i Been leaving in Bali many year .I'm a hotel and restaurant management by trade.i saw one review today of this place saying it was dirty is not true I go there 2 time a week the kitchen is spot les all resto is super clean if you pass in the morning7 .30 every body yuo can see cleaning very well .may be same times by the food is not perfect missing bit of salt but different hand different result .I know I have been working in hospitality for many years.i can't stand people  writing fake reviews.i know well this please is not dirty at all is spot less.people go there and see with your own eyes than judge. name: Villa Ba Jabula
address: Jalan Pantai Seseh, Banjar Pengayahan, Cemagi, Kec. Mengwi, Kabupaten Badung, Bali 80361, Indonesia
review 1:
We, a couple from germany, stayed here in middle of december 2015 in the left bungalow, close to the rice field.

Dubious contact with a little bit lazy owner (Michele, french) who lives at the small property (maybe that is too close?). No introduction or orientation when we arrived. Before bringing us (and luggage) to the room we had to pay cash in Euro. Receipt we got only after double request. If you have any requests (for example we had an problem with the air con) there are only idignant answers or there comes nothing. For example we did ask for surf lessons and they promised to inform us. We never received an answer.

The rice paddies in the area are beautiful but !attention! the farmers work in december is really loud and really disturbs until sunset the whole day. If you stay at the small property (breakfast, pool) and if you need to recover from your stressful job you will get crazy.

The windows are not closable so you need at night eartips due to the unexpected loud nature sounds of rice fields (frogs aso.)

In monsun season some water gets into the bungalow. The bathroom was like a bio hazard after night rain. Bed was also moisty from rain at night.

The beach (dirty & black sand) is at least 15min walk from the bungalows. You can't swim there.

But: nice landscape, nice balinese staff.

Altogether we have to say it is overpriced and the service (not the balinese staff) is bad. We payd 95US$ a night incl. breakfast. You will get a lot more for same money in other places.
review 2: This is no longer an accomodation and is privately owned.
review 3: Very good villa near by seseh beach

name: Burger House Bali
address: Jl. Sukunan No.:2, Cemagi, Kec. Mengwi, Kabupaten Badung, Bali 80351, Indonesia
review 1: I really enjoyed the burger, the beef patty is gigantic and the bun is super fresh and crunchy. The in house spice and sauce is out if this world, totally eat here again luckily it‚Äôs near my home and open till late hours
review 2: ‚ÄúBurger House Bali‚Äù is a recently developed establishment but their food making skills seem to have been honed a over century. A beam of light in this star is the dessert, the ‚ÄúHomemade Snickers,‚Äù as they have a nutty,  chocolatey flavour that explodes in your mouth. Yet another stand out is the ‚ÄúHouse Cheese Burger‚Äù as it‚Äôs juicy patty would put any others to shame. The wait staff were fabulous and the food was cooked quickly and properly leading a great dining experience.
review 3: Tried the single truffle mayo burger, and while the taste is good, the patty is very thin and way too small for the bun (or maybe bun is too big?). The burger did come with a side of fries, so for the price can‚Äôt complain too much.. The cauliflower popcorn however was drenched in sauce and not as crispy as one would expect. That said staff was super friendly and preparation time super fast!
review 4: My perpetual enjoyment of this fine establishment is enforced through its delicious food, extravagant staff and wide variety, which can be suited to any array of western tastes. The spectrum of food goes from the delicious popcorn cauliflower, all the way to the spicy chicken burger, and further to the range of vegan options. I highly recommend!
review 5:
Been living near this place for a while now and finally came to try.

Fantastic burger, nice staff and owner, super chill vibes on the music and the sunset views. Definitely my new burger spot when I get a craving!

name: UMAH - Cemagi
address: Jl. Pantai Seseh, Cemagi, Kec. Mengwi, Kabupaten Badung, Bali 80351, Indonesia
review 1:
Loved this place!

It‚Äôs a modern take on a traditional Indonesian warung. Great vibes and super friendly staff. Definitely worth checking out for tasty food!
review 2: My new favorite spot. Cozy atmosphere, friendly service, and delicious food. Try their rendang and nasi campur. Some of the tastiest I‚Äôve ever had. Highly recommended.
review 3: Best warung around, hands down. Light and clean, great atmosphere and staff. Could eat here EVERY SINGLE DAY. Wish they were all around the island!
review 4: I had a lovely lunch here. The dishes are pre-prepared and are displayed attractively so you can see what you are getting. In particular, I thought the jackfruit curry was very good. While it is true that the servings are relatively small, the low price per portion means that you can try a number of dishes and create yourself a wonderful Indonesian tasting menu for the cost of a single menu item elsewhere. First-rate, healthy, local tastes in pleasant surroundings.
review 5: Incredible new warung that just popped up in the Seseh / Cemagi area. They had a large selection of delicious Indonesian staples and sambal with an actual kick. Will be back often.

name: Giriya Dalem Mandhara Giri
address: Jl. Raya Seseh, Munggu, Kec. Mengwi, Kabupaten Badung, Bali 80351, Indonesia
review 1: beautiful and peaceful. because it is 2.5 hrs from kuta it is not crowded.
review 2: This is probably the most shocking and racist experience I ever needed to make in Bali as a foreigner. I live here and pay Banjar, which is used for ceremonies of the village and the temples. Entering the temple, properly dressed of course, together with my partner we asked an elderly woman  who sat on one of these wooden houses at the temple if we could visit it and pray. She looked at us and I will never forget her expression. She spit on the ground in front of us and screamed: ,,NO! BULE!''. Which means ,,No! Foreigners!'' Bali slowly gets a really reverse racist place and little is left of the once spiritual and positive island. It is not the island of gods anymore but the island of greed. We are very sad that we had such an encounter when there is nothing we did wrong. Why fulfilled with so much hate ?

name: Warung Tamara
address: 94CF+P2P, Jalan Wisata Pantai, Munggu, Kec. Mengwi, Kabupaten Tabanan, Bali 82121, Indonesia
review 1: I stumbled on this undiscovered gem right in our neighboorhood. Everything I tried was bursting with flavor. The decor was unique and incredible. The experience was heavenly as I was served a meal fit for God himself. The waitress did an excellent job. This is definitely a spot I'll be frequenting.
